docs.lead_paragraph: The “Hunger Games” franchise, as did the Harry Potter and “Twilight” series, hopes to demonstrate the art in splitting a final chapter into two installments.

headline.seo: ‘The Hunger Games: Mockingjay Part 1,’ Is the Latest Penultimate Franchise Film
headline.main: Now, the Final Chapter. O.K., Half of It.
headline.print_headline: Now, the Final Chapter. O.K., Half of It.

docs.abstract: The Hunger Games: Mockingjay, Part 1 provides latest example of an epic Hollywood franchise that has decided to split its final chapter into two films; tactic can be successful if films feel worthwhile in their own right, but runs risk of being perceived as a money grab.
docs.snippet: The “Hunger Games” franchise, as did the Harry Potter and “Twilight” series, hopes to demonstrate the art in splitting a final chapter into two installments.

headline.main: Should the United States Declare Books an ‘Essential Good’?
headline.print_headline: The French Government Has Declared Books an ‘Essential Good.’ Should the United States Do the Same?

docs.abstract: Authors Daniel Mendelsohn and Mohsin Hamid consider question of whether the United States should declare books an 'essential good' the way the French government has.
